properties.name: Orchard House
properties.description: Orchard House is the name of the long-standing Massachusetts home of the famous literary family, the Alcotts.  Louisa May Alcott, of 'Little Women' fame, returned to her home, Orchard House, to find inspiration to pen her famous American Classic celebrating the relationship of the four sisters. Therefore the name, not only reflects beauty and heritage, but one of a loving, close-knit family.

properties.name: Meadow View
properties.description: If you are lucky enough to have stunning views of meadows and countryside then this popular house name suggests the tranquillity and natural beauty surrounding your home.

properties.name: Rose Cottage
properties.description: Giving the impression of an idyllic way of life. Far from the hustle and bustle of modern day life. Rose Cottage conjures up associations of a traditional English home set amongst beautiful rose bush gardens.

properties.name: The Hollies
properties.description: Another name steeped in nature and reflective of being surrounded by Holly trees. Invoking an image of being tucked away in glorious countryside â€¦ unless of course you're just a huge 1960s pop fan and wish your home to be named after your favourite band, The Hollies!

properties.name: Old School
properties.description: A less formal version of School House.

properties.name: Primrose Cottage
properties.description: Representative of spring and often found growing wild in woodlands. Primroses create an impression of new life and represent the popular idyllic country atmosphere a lot of homeowners like.

properties.name: The Mill House
properties.description: Following in the footsteps of the high and mighty, tradesmen and workers decided to follow suit and start naming their homes. Traditionally using their trade as inspiration.  So if your home is a former Mill House then this is the perfect name to celebrate its history.

properties.name: Yew Tree Cottage
properties.description: Yew trees are admired for their unique and mysterious appearance. They have represented strength and history since the times of the Druids. They were seen as sacred by spiritual clans.  Thus making this a perfect name for a unique home as well as one built in the presence of a Yew Tree.

properties.name: Oaklands
properties.description: Giving the impression that your home is built amongst a land filled with oak trees.  It creates the impression of many acres and a beautiful view of majestic Oak Trees.

properties.name: Treetops
properties.description: This creates a simple, rustic, natural feel about your home. It suggests the luxury of living amongst the trees.

properties.name: Beside Habitat
properties.description: This unique approach to development may be partially a result of the project's somewhat unconventional genesis. The creation of Beside Habitat was conceived and overseen by the team at Beside, an independent, bilingual magazine and website that covers the intersection of nature and culture.

properties.name: White House
properties.description: Unless situated in Washington, this name purely alludes to the colour of one's home.  However, the associations with the American home of the President also gives this name an air of importance.

properties.name: Haven
properties.description: Meaning a place of safety or sanctuary. Haven is a popular name for a home as it suggests a calm, peaceful abode, where you can hide away from the stresses of the outside world.

properties.name: Fairview
properties.description: If you are lucky enough to have a home overlooking beautiful views then Fairview is an appropriate, albeit rather modest, name for your home.
